I was very disappointed today with the food and service. We always come here often for carnitas and it is about a 30m drive for us and never had a problem.  Today when we got home and opened the carnitas it was a pile of what looked like mush didnt even look appealing. They mixed the meat with pieces of the skin which we didn't ask for skin and never do and it was mixed in so bad we couldn't even separate them. When we called to explain what happened and how our order looked right away the person on the phone says "No they didn't do that". First off mistakes happen in businesses and I of course didn't do it so who else did. I didn't even get an option to bring it back in so they can exchange It. They always have different people working the front and it might have been someone new who didn't know how to serve the carnitas and you would think they might have wanted to check on the person. I understand mistakes can happen but for them to right away not even wanna hear your complaint I think is unprofessional and rude and they need to understand that mistakes do happen even at there location.  I give it a 1 star for Bad customer service no one likes a rude employee and my food today looked disgusting. I would have want to check on my employee who is serving the food if someone would have called to inform me there was something wrong but I guess they didnt.

A very clean and presentable place. Service is amazing. I had the barbacoa and words can’t explain the level of deliciousness. The meat itself with the tortilla is more than enough to make it an awesome dish. Guacamole was also great, it gad of hint of lime which gave it an awesome taste. Its a small place which gives it the feeling of peacefulness as you eat. The scents that come out of this place are delicious. Would definitely recommend to anyone looking for a great authentic Mexican meal. Everybody that works there are very kind and very attentive to your needs. Love the coffee.  Top ten places in Pilsen.

Carnitas are a staple in Mexican cuisine and Sabas knows how to make them not greasy seasoned deliciously and plenty of them. For those of you that don't know what carnitas are go to Sabas. The waitstaff is very friendly and accommodating. Their menu is extensive so you have a great selection. Pilsen is a great experience.
